{"_id":"30lU6qMUbXIkkkWO","name":"Dark Ego - Snow Queen","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Miss Snow and Lady Storm","source":"Lost Stories","category":"hunter","contentKey":"darkego.miss-snow-and-lady-storm","ownerKey":"cazador.miss-snow-and-lady-storm","role":"dark-ego","sequence":0}},"system":{"description":"The tiny fragment of a magic mirror lies in \nyour right eye, relegating the real you to oblivion. But when tears warm your \neyes, or you hear the word that represents your dominion over the cold, Lady \nStorm comes to her senses and woe to those who stand before her.\nWhile you are Lady Storm, you can lower the Soma cost of Snow Sorceress \nby 1 without creating magical accidents. In addition, you can use Winter’s \nKiss at a distance without spending Soma. If you wish, you can summon a \nsnowstorm that will sweep over your location regardless of previous weather \nconditions. Inside the storm, visibility is reduced to about three feet, and all \ninvolved lower their OL by 1 for each action. While the snowstorm rages, you \ncan use the Gift Winter’s Kiss as a free action once per Exchange. This Gift \nends, and the Hunter becomes Miss Snow once more as soon as you suffer 1 \nWound, or at the end of the Scene.","notes":"See bt-ls-hunters-sheets-1.2-eng-BASE-SCREEN.pdf, pages 2.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"Cry over something that genuinely moved you. You hear the word \n“Eternity” spoken by someone who is not aware that it will awaken Lady Storm.","owner":"Miss Snow and Lady Storm","source":"Lost Stories","category":"hunter","key":"darkego.miss-snow-and-lady-storm"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241651,"modifiedTime":1783973241651,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"rkYkGy50uqAWHBtU","name":"Dark Ego - Shattered Pact","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Tremoteus Rumpel","source":"Lost Stories","category":"hunter","contentKey":"darkego.tremoteus-rumpel","ownerKey":"cazador.tremoteus-rumpel","role":"dark-ego","sequence":0}},"system":{"description":"Those who break the rules must be \npunished. Y ou gain 1 Additional Success on all Position and Defense \nChecks you make against a subject who’s acting in a way that contradicts \nthe statement you recorded using the For the Record effect. If you act \nto harm them, you also inflict 1 Additional Wound. Once per Scene, if \na subject reveals themselves as they really are, as opposed to how they \npreviously presented themselves, or if they break their word, you can \nlecture them on their dishonesty. All your companions gain 1 Additional \nSuccess on their next action.","notes":"See bt-ls-hunters-sheets-1.2-eng-BASE-SCREEN.pdf, pages 4.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"Make an argument against the guilty by pointing out their \nmisdeeds.","owner":"Tremoteus Rumpel","source":"Lost Stories","category":"hunter","key":"darkego.tremoteus-rumpel"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241652,"modifiedTime":1783973241652,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"Si3HofAoyFRqcHro","name":"Dark Ego - Oknytt’s Legacy","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Prince Trollo the Innocent","source":"Lost Stories","category":"hunter","contentKey":"darkego.prince-trollo-the-innocent","ownerKey":"cazador.prince-trollo-the-innocent","role":"dark-ego","sequence":0}},"system":{"description":"Y ou appeal to your Dark Ego to gain \ngreat powers. If it is day, you must spend 1 Soma. If you have no Soma, \nyou take 1 Wound. If it is night, there is no cost to activate this Gift, as \nyou are a creature of the night. Y ou gain the following powers:\n1. Yellow Eyes: See perfectly in total darkness. Once per Scene, you can \nsee a target for what they really are, unmasking any disguise they may \nbe wearing. \n2. Troll Strength: Once per Scene, you can perform an act of unprecedented strength by lifting or moving a weight equal to ten men. If you \nuse your strength to harm someone, you inflict 1 Additional Wound. \n3. Stone Skin: Once per Scene, you can suffer an attack or hazard while \navoiding any Wounds. Y ou can resist almost everything, including fire, \nfalls, and weapons. Only magic can harm you. Y ou must declare the use \nof this effect before any Defense Check.","notes":"See bt-ls-hunters-sheets-1.2-eng-BASE-SCREEN.pdf, pages 6.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"You tap into your heritage in front of someone you have helped \nbefore and who is unaware of your true nature.","owner":"Prince Trollo the Innocent","source":"Lost Stories","category":"hunter","key":"darkego.prince-trollo-the-innocent"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241652,"modifiedTime":1783973241652,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"jrhciskWJEFbXPph","name":"Dark Ego - The Magic of Disbelief","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Pietrik and the Cauldron Fae","source":"Lost Stories","category":"hunter","contentKey":"darkego.pietrik-and-the-cauldron-fae","ownerKey":"cazador.pietrik-and-the-cauldron-fae","role":"dark-ego","sequence":0}},"system":{"description":"The Cauldron Fae unleashes \nher magic to enable you to perform amazing actions. As an action, \nyou can formulate a magic sentence including the fragment I don’t \nbelieve and make its effect concrete. For example, “I don’t believe in \ngravity” would allow you to fly, while “I don’t believe the Hunters of \nthe Order exist” would allow you to hurt the Hunters in an attempt to \nmake them disappear. If your statement has no offensive effect, spend \n1 Soma to gain the power you summoned for the entire Scene. On \nthe other hand, if you want the spell to affect a target \nother than yourself, spend 1 Soma \nto inflict a Wound or apply the effect without making a Check. Each \ntime you use the Magic of Disbelief, roll a die. On a roll of 5 or 6, the \nStoryteller gains 1 Prank Token. The Storyteller can spend 1 Prank \nToken during a Scene to activate the effect of this Gift (you do not take a \nWound because the Activator was not normally triggered) and have the \nCauldron Fae cast a spell to complicate your life or attempt to damage \nsomething that represents progress and modernity. If the Storyteller has \nno accumulated Prank Tokens, you may choose to ignore all the Soma \ncosts to activate the effects of this Gift, but the Storyteller will gain 1 \nPrank Token.","notes":"See bt-ls-hunters-sheets-1.2-eng-BASE-SCREEN.pdf, pages 8.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"Without thinking about the possible consequences, throw \nyourself into an action that is impossible for an ordinary person.","owner":"Pietrik and the Cauldron Fae","source":"Lost Stories","category":"hunter","key":"darkego.pietrik-and-the-cauldron-fae"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241652,"modifiedTime":1783973241652,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"OCVoWul6I2aizlZm","name":"Dark Ego - The Great Deception","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Loki the Deceiver","source":"Lost Stories","category":"hunter","contentKey":"darkego.loki-the-deceiver","ownerKey":"cazador.loki-the-deceiver","role":"dark-ego","sequence":0}},"system":{"description":"The whole world is a lie, and only \nthose who are truly aware of it can pull the strings of any story. During \nthe course of the Scene, you can activate each of the following effects \nonce:\n1. Materialize an item that is useful for the situation you are facing and \nthat an ally of yours is carrying without knowing it.\n2. Switch places with a Minor NPC. The exchange takes place in the \nblink of an eye, and those present will only see where you are now \nand where your target has ended up. Highly skilled NPCs and other \nHunters are immune to this effect.\n3. Make an NPC that you have met before appear in the Scene. This is \nan illusion that will do your bidding and will dissolve as soon as it \ntakes 1 Wound or it becomes clear that it is not the real person.\n4. Gain 1 Additional Success in a Check you make by exploiting a \nsubject’s character flaw.","notes":"See bt-ls-hunters-sheets-1.2-eng-BASE-SCREEN.pdf, pages 10.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"Organize a deception by studying it in detail, or expose a \ndeception to the people being deceived.","owner":"Loki the Deceiver","source":"Lost Stories","category":"hunter","key":"darkego.loki-the-deceiver"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241653,"modifiedTime":1783973241653,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"sQpKhIfFl436Ij6j","name":"Dark Ego - The Caring Mother","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Silent Mother","source":"Lost Stories","category":"hunter","contentKey":"darkego.the-silent-mother","ownerKey":"cazador.the-silent-mother","role":"dark-ego","sequence":0}},"system":{"description":"Choose a female NPC or Hunter \nand name her your Pupil. Y our Pupil must be young and, in your \nopinion, deserving of your benevolence. Y ou will always know where \nyour Pupil is, and she will gain 1 Additional Success to her actions (or \nincrease her OL by 1 in the case of an NPC) if you are present in the \nScene to comfort her with your words. Y ou get 1 Additional Success if \nyou act against someone who endangers your Pupil. If an NPC or Hunter \nuses a Gift to harm your disciple, you can spend 1 Soma to prevent the \nGift from being activated.","notes":"See bt-ls-hunters-sheets-1.2-eng-BASE-SCREEN.pdf, pages 12.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"Your words inspire a young girl to find her way or protect her \nfrom injustice.","owner":"The Silent Mother","source":"Lost Stories","category":"hunter","key":"darkego.the-silent-mother"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241653,"modifiedTime":1783973241653,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"X0SxHR64azshj6Lj","name":"Dark Ego - You Are What You Fight","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Karasu Kuroi the Wandering Monk","source":"Lost Stories","category":"hunter","contentKey":"darkego.karasu-kuroi-the-wandering-monk","ownerKey":"cazador.karasu-kuroi-the-wandering-monk","role":"dark-ego","sequence":0}},"system":{"description":"When you reveal your true nature, \nyour body changes into the form of a humanoid raven. Y ou will gain the \nfollowing abilities:\n1. Y ou can move by flying thanks to the large wings on your back. Y ou gain \n1 Additional Success on all Defense Checks while hovering in the air. \n2. Y ou can use your large beak to strike an enemy as an additional action, \nbut you cannot communicate by speaking.\n3. Y ou gain 1 Additional Success if you act to injure someone who has \ninflicted 1 Wound on you in the current Scene.","notes":"See bt-ls-hunters-sheets-1.2-eng-BASE-SCREEN.pdf, pages 14.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"You reveal your true nature to prove that not all spirits are evil.","owner":"Karasu Kuroi the Wandering Monk","source":"Lost Stories","category":"hunter","key":"darkego.karasu-kuroi-the-wandering-monk"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241654,"modifiedTime":1783973241654,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"o5RUBtNKdP7j6JiU","name":"Dark Ego - Heigh-ho, Heigh-ho","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The 7 Hessian Mercenaries","source":"Lost Stories","category":"hunter","contentKey":"darkego.the-7-hessian-mercenaries","ownerKey":"cazador.the-7-hessian-mercenaries","role":"dark-ego","sequence":0}},"system":{"description":"If you are preparing for a confrontation, \nno one can stand up to you. If it is on a mission, the Support Team immediately \nre-enters the Scene (even if it means interrupting another task assigned through \nthe On Mission Gift), with all the narrative benefits that can bring. For the rest \nof the Scene, the Main and Support Teams will act as a single Hunter 2 times \nper Exchange, not consecutively. Any personal Gifts from the various members \nmay be used.","notes":"See bt-ls-hunters-sheets-1.2-eng-BASE-SCREEN.pdf, pages 16.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"Begin a confrontation or challenge with the singing of your battle \nhymn.","owner":"The 7 Hessian Mercenaries","source":"Lost Stories","category":"hunter","key":"darkego.the-7-hessian-mercenaries"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241654,"modifiedTime":1783973241654,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"muizoCPq8B0cqXUq","name":"Dark Ego - Goddess Blood","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Circe the Alchemist","source":"Lost Stories","category":"hunter","contentKey":"darkego.circe-the-alchemist","ownerKey":"cazador.circe-the-alchemist","role":"dark-ego","sequence":0}},"system":{"description":"Y ou have the power of a goddess within you, \neven if you do not know how to use it. When you activate your aura, you \nchoose an NPC who will be kind to you and try to fulfill your every wish. This \nGift will have no effect on someone who has hostile intentions towards you, \nbut you will gain 2 Additional Successes on all Defense Checks you make, \nsince harming you seems an unnatural action even to those who hate you.\nY ou can activate all of the Travel Companion Gift’s effects on Eurylochus at \nthe same time.","notes":"See bt-ls-hunters-sheets-1.2-eng-BASE-SCREEN.pdf, pages 20.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"Unleash your divine power with a charming or swaggering attitude \nat the most inopportune moment.","owner":"Circe the Alchemist","source":"Lost Stories","category":"hunter","key":"darkego.circe-the-alchemist"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241655,"modifiedTime":1783973241655,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"lcWPwyvpJRdSPAGg","name":"Dark Ego - Capture the Outlaws","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Captain William of Nottingham","source":"Lost Stories","category":"hunter","contentKey":"darkego.captain-william-of-nottingham","ownerKey":"cazador.captain-william-of-nottingham","role":"dark-ego","sequence":0}},"system":{"description":"Under your leadership, evildoers \nare short-lived. Receive 2 Taxes Tokens. At any time during the Scene, \nyou can spend 1 Taxes Token to activate the following additional effects. \nEach effect can only be activated once per Exchange:\n1. Allow one of your allies to act immediately to carry out one of your \norders, even if they have already acted in the Exchange.\n2. Gain 2 Additional Successes for any action you take to stop (not \neliminate) a criminal or prevent his escape.\n3. Reveal an aspect of an NPC’s private business to your advantage, \nsuch as a connection to another NPC or what they are trying to \nprotect at all costs.","notes":"See bt-ls-hunters-sheets-1.2-eng-BASE-SCREEN.pdf, pages 22.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"Act to capture or render harmless subjects you deem evil.","owner":"Captain William of Nottingham","source":"Lost Stories","category":"hunter","key":"darkego.captain-william-of-nottingham"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241655,"modifiedTime":1783973241655,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"dctqlxgg8ITLwkAZ","name":"Dark Ego - The Napoleon of Crime","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Moriarty the Gentleman Thief","source":"Lost Stories Exclusives","category":"hunter","contentKey":"darkego.moriarty-the-gentleman-thief","ownerKey":"cazador.moriarty-the-gentleman-thief","role":"dark-ego","sequence":0}},"system":{"description":"When you reveal your plan in \nall its glory, the unsuspecting pawns of your game will be left speechless. \nY ou will receive 2 Spider Web Tokens. Y ou can spend them as if they \nwere Soma points. Y ou can also activate the following effects at any time \nin the Scene at a cost of 1 Spider Web Token each:\n1. Discovering the Gift of an NPC. \n2. Allow an ally to activate their Dark Ego by ignoring the Activator. \n3. Provide 1 Additional Success to an Ally’s Position Check.","notes":"See Broken Tales - Lost Stories - Exclusive Pre-Gen Hunters.pdf, pages 2.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"Announce your plan loudly. Show everyone that what you \nhave done before has created an advantage in the current situation.","owner":"Moriarty the Gentleman Thief","source":"Lost Stories Exclusives","category":"hunter","key":"darkego.moriarty-the-gentleman-thief"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241655,"modifiedTime":1783973241655,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"f0fMh4qYHJx5NuVn","name":"Dark Ego - The Vampire","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Pale Medic","source":"Lost Stories Exclusives","category":"hunter","contentKey":"darkego.the-pale-medic","ownerKey":"cazador.the-pale-medic","role":"dark-ego","sequence":0}},"system":{"description":"Self-inflict 1 Wound and release the power of \nthe ancient curse that permeates your body. Y ou gain 1 Additional Success for \neach Position Check you make using your supernatural power. Y ou can use \neach of the following powers once per Scene:\n1. Turn into a cloud of mist. In this form, you will move slowly but can \navoid all obstacles. While in this form, you retain all your senses, can \nonly be injured by magic, and cannot physically interact with objects or \npeople.\n2. Summon three wolves that will act under your total control. The wolves \nare Minor NPCs with the following profiles: \nOL Medium 5 - (1 Wound) - Descriptor: I am a big wild wolf, ready to \nfight to the death for my master. \n3. Communicate telepathically with another person on whom you used one \nof your Gifts during the Scenario.","notes":"See Broken Tales - Lost Stories - Exclusive Pre-Gen Hunters.pdf, pages 4.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"Drink and savor human blood in front of someone. Alternatively, \nbreak a crucifix or throw away garlic in disgust.","owner":"The Pale Medic","source":"Lost Stories Exclusives","category":"hunter","key":"darkego.the-pale-medic"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241656,"modifiedTime":1783973241656,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"56xXU4GmoiiwBJgW","name":"Dark Ego - Alien Technology","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Respectable Mr. and Mrs. Mars","source":"Lost Stories Exclusives","category":"hunter","contentKey":"darkego.the-respectable-mr-and-mrs-mars","ownerKey":"cazador.the-respectable-mr-and-mrs-mars","role":"dark-ego","sequence":0}},"system":{"description":"Y ou can always take advantage of your \nspecial Equipment:\n1. Laser Pistol: An accurate and silent firearm capable of ignoring all \ncommon defenses. Wounds inflicted cannot be healed until the end of the \nScenario. When a target is eliminated, it becomes a pile of ashes and cannot be \nhealed, even with special Gifts.\n2. Fog Generator: Instantly creates a thick black smoke that blocks the \nvisibility of non-aliens. The smoke lasts for a few minutes but can be quickly \ndispersed by a strong wind.\n3. Portable Tripod: A small multifunctional vehicle that moves on three legs \nand can carry up to six passengers. The Tripod can reach up to nine feet in \nheight and can easily avoid obstacles thanks to its flexible legs. \nWhenever you use alien technology and one or more NPCs witness it, you \nget 1 Invasion! Token. At the end of each Scene in which you have used the \nDark Ego, the Storyteller rolls 1 die for each Invasion! Token. If they roll at \nleast one 6, the Invasion! Tokens are reset and your comrades initiate an attack \non Earth. The Storyteller introduces 4 Martian Agents into the Scenario, who, \nif not eliminated by the end of it, will force you to return to the Operations \nCenter, removing you from the current Campaign.\nMartian Agent - OL Medium 5 - (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am an alien skilled in guerrilla warfare. My monstrous appearance \nparalyzes foolish humans with terror. \nAgenda: Eliminate all humans, starting with the most dangerous individuals: \nthe Hunters of the Order.\nGift - Armed for Invasion: A Martian Agent can use a single effect of Alien \nTechnology 1 time per Scene.","notes":"See Broken Tales - Lost Stories - Exclusive Pre-Gen Hunters.pdf, pages 6.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"Show off your alien nature by using strange technology or revealing \nyour true identity.","owner":"The Respectable Mr. and Mrs. Mars","source":"Lost Stories Exclusives","category":"hunter","key":"darkego.the-respectable-mr-and-mrs-mars"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241656,"modifiedTime":1783973241656,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"xEjdCEdWMF2Ud6Qk","name":"Dark Ego - Reanimator","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Doctor V. Frankenstein","source":"Lost Stories Exclusives","category":"hunter","contentKey":"darkego.doctor-v-frankenstein","ownerKey":"cazador.doctor-v-frankenstein","role":"dark-ego","sequence":0}},"system":{"description":"Y ou appeal to the power of science to bring \nlife where there is none. Y ou receive 3 Reanimator Tokens. At your touch, \nand by spending 1 Reanimator Token, an inanimate object or corpse will \ncome to life for the duration of the Scene. Decide whether to also spend \n1 Soma to gain control of what you have animated, or to allow this new \ncreature to have free will. The Storyteller will create an NPC profile for \nhumans and animals (including the reanimation of a single part, such as \na hand or leg), or a Threat profile in the case of an inanimate object, such \nas a door or rope. If you are in control, the creation will do whatever you \ntell it to do. If the creation is acting with free will, it will be moved by the \nStoryteller and may even turn against you.","notes":"See Broken Tales - Lost Stories - Exclusive Pre-Gen Hunters.pdf, pages 8.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"Dismember or dig up a corpse, ignoring the horror it may cause \nthose watching.","owner":"Doctor V. Frankenstein","source":"Lost Stories Exclusives","category":"hunter","key":"darkego.doctor-v-frankenstein"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241657,"modifiedTime":1783973241657,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"Y4QvofH5Zh00oCU1","name":"Dark Ego - Water Fairy","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Lost Stories Exclusives Hunter 5","source":"Lost Stories Exclusives","category":"hunter","contentKey":"darkego.lost-stories-exclusives-hunter-5","ownerKey":"cazador.lost-stories-exclusives-hunter-5","role":"dark-ego","sequence":0}},"system":{"description":"Y ou can spend 1 Soma to create 2 small pools \nof lake water, three feet wide and five inches deep. The pools will be created \non any surface, and you can create them anywhere within your field of vision. \nWhen you dip your feet into the water, you unleash your thousand-year-old \nfairy powers. Y ou can choose one of these effects as an additional action in \nany Exchange:\n1. Recover 1 Wound you suffered during this Scene.\n2. Move immediately to a place that you can see. No one can stop you, but \nyou must end up with your feet in contact with the water.\n3. Create a dense fog from a water source that limits visibility but has no \neffect on you.\n4. Hit a target with a jet of water from a pool you create. This is a normal \nattack that requires a Position Check and causes 1 Wound.","notes":"See Broken Tales - Lost Stories - Exclusive Pre-Gen Hunters.pdf, pages 10.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"Dive into the water of a lake and drop your disguise, or give advice \nto someone you really care about.","owner":"Lost Stories Exclusives Hunter 5","source":"Lost Stories Exclusives","category":"hunter","key":"darkego.lost-stories-exclusives-hunter-5"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241657,"modifiedTime":1783973241657,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"UWvbo86UcVemkzus","name":"Dark Ego - Taking Destiny into My Own Hands","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Lost Stories Exclusives Hunter 6","source":"Lost Stories Exclusives","category":"hunter","contentKey":"darkego.lost-stories-exclusives-hunter-6","ownerKey":"cazador.lost-stories-exclusives-hunter-6","role":"dark-ego","sequence":0}},"system":{"description":"Nothing and no one \ncan hold you against your will. Y ou are free from all obstacles and can move \nat any time, even in the midst of battle, without anyone being able to block \nor harm you. By spending 1 Soma, you can automatically break down any \nenvironmental obstacle in your way, such as walls, doors, or a tangled web of \nbrambles. Y our presence undermines the authority of the powerful: all NPCs \ntied to any kind of authority lower their OL by 1; all Hunters tied to faith or \nwith strong leadership skills receive 1 Penalty per Check.","notes":"See Broken Tales - Lost Stories - Exclusive Pre-Gen Hunters.pdf, pages 12.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"Stand up for someone being oppressed, or openly denounce those \nwho hold power over you.\nEquipment: \nA staff sprouting tendrils / A large bar of soap / A sharp razor / A small \npitcher of water / A perfectly polished rock / A light crossbow / A golden \nearring.\nSoma\n 6\nXP\nWounds \n1.\n2.\n3.\nExtra \nWound.\nI am the Princess of Altomonte, and I succeeded my father by taking full control of his lands. I have always rebelled against the old laws \nof the past, which placed all power in the hands of men. The strength of my ideas was unyielding, leading me to carry out serious acts of \nreprisal against the noble families most tied to the old patriarchal traditions. The Order intervened to stop me, but when they realized that \ntaking me prisoner would make me a martyr, I was offered a deal: join the ranks of the Order to fight the darkness. In exchange, I have \nbeen promised favors and political power with which to change the male-dominated society of my era forever.","owner":"Lost Stories Exclusives Hunter 6","source":"Lost Stories Exclusives","category":"hunter","key":"darkego.lost-stories-exclusives-hunter-6"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241658,"modifiedTime":1783973241658,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"lDHJJODVXd2K1Ig0","name":"Dark Ego - Infallible Cunning","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Lost Stories Exclusives Hunter 7","source":"Lost Stories Exclusives","category":"hunter","contentKey":"darkego.lost-stories-exclusives-hunter-7","ownerKey":"cazador.lost-stories-exclusives-hunter-7","role":"dark-ego","sequence":0}},"system":{"description":"When you activate this Gift, the \nStoryteller will reveal to you the Downside of all NPCs in the Scene. \nY ou’ll also learn the easiest way to escape from your location and the most \nvaluable item present. When a Hunter (including you) performs a Check \nand gets a Standard Outcome, you can spend 1 Soma to add 1 Increment \nof your choice, including a special effect of a Gift possessed by the Hunter \nperforming the action.","notes":"See Broken Tales - Lost Stories - Exclusive Pre-Gen Hunters.pdf, pages 14.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"Take a few minutes to observe the situation and tell the NPC in \nfront of you what you really think of them. \nEquipment: \nA bag of white pebbles / Seven small gold crowns / Valuable coins and \njewels / A mask with the features of an ogre / A pair of valuable traveling \nboots with two hidden stilettos / Contracts and records of secret negotiations \n/ The key to one of your many secret hideouts / A sling. \nSoma\n 6\nXP\nWounds \n1.\n2.\n3.\nExtra \nWound.\nI am the most important criminal of my time, and there are more than a thousand scoundrels in my employ. I have \nsingle-handedly built up my power through cunning, even committing acts that many people consider despicable. \nThose who lecture me on my misdeeds do not understand that the only thing I wanted in my life was a family that loved \nme. The Order disrupted my criminal empire, but when they realized that eliminating me would start a war among \noutlaws across Europe, I was pardoned and welcomed as a Hunter. My gifts and knowledge ensure a constant flow \nof information, which I use to track down whatever the Order is hunting. Locked away in the fortress of my solitude, I \ncontinue to run my empire. Perhaps I can find a true family in the ranks of the Hunters.","owner":"Lost Stories Exclusives Hunter 7","source":"Lost Stories Exclusives","category":"hunter","key":"darkego.lost-stories-exclusives-hunter-7"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241658,"modifiedTime":1783973241658,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"pBRa4QpyyF0InkPM","name":"Dark Ego - It’s Time to Kill the Beast","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Lost Stories Exclusives Hunter 8","source":"Lost Stories Exclusives","category":"hunter","contentKey":"darkego.lost-stories-exclusives-hunter-8","ownerKey":"cazador.lost-stories-exclusives-hunter-8","role":"dark-ego","sequence":0}},"system":{"description":"Once per Scene, if you make an \nattack against an enemy with monstrous characteristics, you automatically \nhit without a Check and your attack inflicts 2 Wounds. All of the Wounds \nyou inflict leave clearly visible marks and cannot be healed by the victim \nuntil the end of the Scenario. When you activate this Gift, the Storyteller will \nreveal to you one Gift of each monstrous opponent in the Scene. \nNote: A “monstrous trait” is defined as any Hunter or NPC with Gifts or \nDescriptors that represent superhuman physical traits and abilities that also \ngive them a monstrous appearance. However, the Storyteller has the final say \non whether or not a Character is monstrous.","notes":"See Broken Tales - Lost Stories - Exclusive Pre-Gen Hunters.pdf, pages 16.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"Openly challenge a monstrous creature by revealing your true nature.\nEquipment: \nThe right weapon for each beast / A cloak that changes color according to \nits surroundings / A small leaf-shaped ocarina / Animal traps / A deer heart \npreserved under spirits / A necklace of wolf fangs. \nSoma\n 6\nXP\nWounds \n1.\n2.\n3.\nExtra \nWound.\nI am a lone beast slayer who has dedicated his entire life to eradicating monsters and aberrations. The \nOne Who Plots in the Shadows corrupted my soul by drawing on the pain of the monsters’ poor victims I \ncould not save. The Order has freed me from this evil influence and welcomed me into its ranks as a strong \narm against all manner of monsters. I do not like to talk or waste time with complicated plans: when it is \ntime to begin the hunt, having my weapons ready is all that matters.","owner":"Lost Stories Exclusives Hunter 8","source":"Lost Stories Exclusives","category":"hunter","key":"darkego.lost-stories-exclusives-hunter-8"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241658,"modifiedTime":1783973241658,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"vziYOkAVgR3fsD2C","name":"Dark Ego - All Eyes on Me","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Lost Stories Exclusives Hunter 9","source":"Lost Stories Exclusives","category":"hunter","contentKey":"darkego.lost-stories-exclusives-hunter-9","ownerKey":"cazador.lost-stories-exclusives-hunter-9","role":"dark-ego","sequence":0}},"system":{"description":"When you choose to be the center of \nattention, you are the king of the party. Decide what you want to wear and \nwhat valuables you want to display, and you will look the part. Y ou will also \nreceive the following benefits:\n1. All NPCs present will be favorably disposed toward you, and you can \ncreate an Agenda for one of them to represent their strong interest in \nyou. Particularly powerful subjects may require a Position Check, at the \nStoryteller’s discretion. \n2. If a lie is told in your presence, the person who told it suffers 1 Wound \ncaused by bleeding from the eyes.\n3. If you help someone permanently improve the aesthetics of a person or \nplace, you gain 1 Soma. \nThe effect of this Gift lasts until the end of the Scene or until you activate \nanother of your Gifts.","notes":"See Broken Tales - Lost Stories - Exclusive Pre-Gen Hunters.pdf, pages 18.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"trigger":"Take a few minutes to prepare for a meeting with someone you \ndeem important. \nEquipment: \nThe precious crown that I always wear on my head. \nSoma\n 5\nXP\nWounds \n1.\n2.\n3.\nExtra \nWound.\nI was a vain ruler and had eyes only for beauty. My heart was pure and my desire to help others was \nsincere, but everyone took advantage of me and clouded my vision with false words. Seeing beyond the wall \nof lies cost me dearly, but now I am not afraid. I see everything as it is, even myself. The Order hired me as a \nHunter, asking only that I use my power in the service of justice, without ulterior motives, without falsehood. \nBut is that really the case? I no longer care, for now, the only truth that matters to me is the one I choose to \ncreate with my mind.","owner":"Lost Stories Exclusives Hunter 9","source":"Lost Stories Exclusives","category":"hunter","key":"darkego.lost-stories-exclusives-hunter-9"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241659,"modifiedTime":1783973241659,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
